1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:15,000
When Jesus comes in glory,

2
00:00:15,000 --> 00:00:30,000
As Lord and King of kings,

3
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:45,000
O what a wondrous story

4
00:00:45,000 --> 00:01:00,000
The blessed Bible brings:

5
00:01:00,000 --> 00:01:15,000
His face will shine like the sunlight,

6
00:01:15,000 --> 00:01:30,000
His head be white as snow,

7
00:01:30,000 --> 00:01:45,000
His eyes like flaming firelight,

8
00:01:45,000 --> 00:02:00,000
His feet like brass aglow.

9
00:02:00,000 --> 00:02:15,000
His voice like rushing waters

10
00:02:15,000 --> 00:02:30,000
Will reach with mighty sound

11
00:02:30,000 --> 00:02:45,000
Into the deepest quarters

12
00:02:45,000 --> 00:03:00,000
Of all creation round;

13
00:03:00,000 --> 00:03:15,000
And at this wondrous greeting

14
00:03:15,000 --> 00:03:30,000
The dead in Christ shall rise,

15
00:03:30,000 --> 00:03:45,000
Their Lord and Saviour meeting

16
00:03:45,000 --> 00:04:00,000
In glory in the skies.

17
00:04:00,000 --> 00:04:15,000
And we who believing

18
00:04:15,000 --> 00:04:30,000
And His appearing love,

19
00:04:30,000 --> 00:04:45,000
Shall know we are receiving

20
00:04:45,000 --> 00:05:00,000
His glory from above;

21
00:05:00,000 --> 00:05:15,000
His resurrection power

22
00:05:15,000 --> 00:05:30,000
Will raise us to the place

23
00:05:30,000 --> 00:05:45,000
Where we that wondrous hour

24
00:05:45,000 --> 00:06:00,000
Shall see Him face to face.

25
00:06:00,000 --> 00:06:15,000
O hasten Thine appearing

26
00:06:15,000 --> 00:06:30,000
Thou bright and Morning Star!

27
00:06:30,000 --> 00:06:45,000
Lord, may we soon be hearing

28
00:06:45,000 --> 00:07:00,000
The trumpet sound afar;

29
00:07:00,000 --> 00:07:15,000
They people all are yearning

30
00:07:15,000 --> 00:07:30,000
To be Thy raptured bride,

31
00:07:30,000 --> 00:07:45,000
To be Thy own returning

32
00:07:45,000 --> 00:08:00,000
Be caught up to Thy side.

